<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 11:13PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Moore,
Montgomery and northeastern Stanly Counties through MIDNIGHT EDT...
At 1113 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Albemarle, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Troy, Badin Lake, Biscoe, Plyler, Norwood, Badin, Mount
Gilead, Star and Candor.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 600 AM EDT for
central North Carolina.</instruction>
